subSubSection.paragraph:
(Plate I: figs 
1–7
)

Pronotum longitudinally campaniform, almost straight laterally, along median line distinctly longer than wide across posterior angles (length: 3.0 mm, width: 
2.3 mm
), slightly arched medially and declined to base; pronotum with shallow oval median groove from base to apex, lateral edges slightly arched; posterior angles divergent with a distinct apically cuspidate carina (fig. 
3
), apex obtuse (arrow, fig 
3
); pronotal lateral edges completely visible in dorsal view; pronotal punctures medially and laterally umbilicate with interstices equal to one or half puncture diameter (fig. 
2
), pronotal surface micro-reticulated; pubescence bent from median line to apex and to lateral sides.

Elytra subparallel, becoming very slightly narrower subapically, elytral apex arcuately bent (fig. 
6
), apically with a short thorn on each elytron (arrow, fig 
6
); base very slightly shorter than pronotal posterior angles, slightly depressed at scutellum, margins arched, shoulders prominent (winged species); elytral striae with distinct deep punctures, their interstices with smaller and fine punctures, conspicuously micro-reticulated and transversely rugose (fig. 
4
); pubescence short, bristly, declined to apex and to lateral sides.

Aedeagus long and elongate (fig. 
7
); penis subparallel, subapically distinctly constricted, slightly exceeding paramere apices; parameres apically very slightly cochleariform, laterally slightly concave (arrow, fig 
7
).
